    "message_1": "What is the number of iterations required for the point (-0.3, 0.6) to escape from the Mandelbrot set?",
    "message_2": "To determine the number of iterations required for the point (-0.3, 0.6) to escape the Mandelbrot set, we need to apply the iterative formula for the Mandelbrot set:\n\nZₙ₊₁ = Zₙ² + C\n\nwhere Zₙ is a complex number, C is the complex constant (-0.3 + 0.6i), and Z₀ = 0.\n\nWe will iterate this formula until the magnitude of Zₙ (|Zₙ|) is greater than 2, which is the condition for a point to escape the Mandelbrot set.\n\nIteration 1:\nZ₁ = Z₀² + C = 0² + (-0.3 + 0.6i) = -0.3 + 0.6i\n\n|Z₁| = √((-0.3)² + (0.6)²) = √(0.09 + 0.36) = √0.45 ≈ 0.67\n\nIteration 2:\nZ₂ = Z₁² + C = (-0.3 + 0.6i)² + (-0.3 + 0.6i) = (0.45 - 0.36) + (0.6 - 0.18)i = 0.09 + 0.42i\n\n|Z₂| = √((0.09)² + (0.42)²) = √(0.0081 + 0.1764) = √0.1845 ≈ 0.43\n\nIteration 3:\nZ₃ = Z₂² + C = (0.09 + 0.42i)² + (-0.3 + 0.6i) = (-0.1716 + 0.0756) + (0.0756 + 0.498)i = -0.096 + 0.5736i\n\n|Z₃| = √((-0.096)² + (0.5736)²) = √(0.009216 + 0.32899296) = √0.33820896 ≈ 0.58\n\nIteration 4:\nZ₄ = Z₃² + C = (-0.096 + 0.5736i)² + (-0.3 + 0.6i) = (0.331776 - 0.110016) + (0.109824 + 0.449856)i = 0.22176 + 0.55968i\n\n|Z₄| = √((0.22176)² + (0.55968)²) = √(0.0491778176 + 0.3132001024) = √0.36237792 ≈ 0.60\n\nIteration 5:\nZ₅ = Z₄² + C = (0.22176 + 0.55968i)² + (-0.3 + 0.6i) = (-0.09241664 + 0.24736064) + (0.24736064 + 0.49344032)i = 0.154944 + 0.740801i\n\n|Z₅| = √((0.154944)² + (0.740801)²) = √(0.0239992836 + 0.5483865601) = √0.5723858437 ≈ 0.76\n\nIteration 6:\nZ₆ = Z₅² + C = (0.154944 + 0.740801i)² + (-0.3 + 0.6i) = (-0.3969641281 + 0.2290561281) + (0.2290561281 + 0.8817122562)i = -0.167908 + 1.110768i\n\n|Z₆| = √((-0.167908)² + (1.110768)²) = √(0.0281786464 + 1.2338029824) = √1.2619816288 ≈ 1.12\n\nIteration 7:\nZ₇ = Z₆² + C = (-0.167908 + 1.110768i)² + (-0.3 + 0.6i) = (-1.035732 + 0.372164) + (0.372164 + 1.482804)i = -0.663568 + 2.052804i\n\n|Z₇| = √((-0.663568)² + (2.052804)²) = √(0.4403229824 + 4.2135020544) = √4.6538250368 ≈ 2.16\n\nSince |Z₇| > 2, the point (-0.3, 0.6) escapes the Mandelbrot set after 7 iterations."
